name: places/ChIJa1WN9dob2jERWFxNMq2ZVgM/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQ5aVliWDF3RRAB
text: {'text': 'This is one of the hill parks in Singapore and part of the Singapore Southern Ridge . The park is popular with locals and tourists alike as it is a convenient access to the Henderson Wave, a popular tourist attraction where get to see the neighboring area at a high elevation. Further on from the Henderson Wave is  another tourist attraction - Mount Faber Park. At Mount Faber Park you can take the Cable Car to yet another tourist attraction - Sentosa Island. For those who prefers to walk, there is a trail leading to Vivocity, which is a bridge away from Sentosa.\n\nYou can also walk from Telok Blangah Hill Park to another tourist attraction - Hort Park .', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJa1WN9dob2jERWFxNMq2ZVgM/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNkc2VybDJRRRAB
text: {'text': 'Telok Blangah Hill Park is a park situated at Telok Blangah Green, off Henderson Road, in Bukit Merah. The most awesome features of this park are Henderson Waves Bridge linking it to Mount Faber Park and the Forest Walk which is a 1.3km elevated pedestrian bridge that enables you to walk among lush secondary forest canopy.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJa1WN9dob2jERWFxNMq2ZVgM/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR1eG9QbE9REAE
text:
{'text': 'Visit the hill park during weekday evening.

Take grab and alight at car park, very easy to spot the the hill.

Attach photo do show that is not many people around during weekday.

Top of the hill really windy, nice place to relax to chit chat with your close one.

Disappointed that there is no "bed of flower" during the visit, maybe not the season or something else.', 'languageCode': 'en'}
